who are we to decide it's our pet's time to go please help me i am in a extreme guilt ever since i euthanized my year old dog last year in december he was suffering with advanced kidney failure he was throwing up stoped eating completely and loosing weight and he had been taking medicine for congestive heart failure had a heart murmur he used to have good days and bad days one day he could not sit or lay down b c all fluid was spreding in his lungs because of heart failure so when his doc said he is suffering with adv kidney failure and there is nothingmuch they can't od about it either put him on iv for temporary relief or euthanize him i chose the second option to put him down and end his suffering i don't know if he was in pain but he was not eating at all and throwing up a lot that time as a pet owner i think i did the right thing b c i loved him dearly like my own baby but later i felt extreme guilt i feel like i murdered my beloved dog how can i take this guilt away did i do the right thing if so who r we to decide it euthanasia is actually more of a luxury for pets who are dying and miserable they can't tell us where it hurts or how to make it better like people can imagine in the wild when animals are sick trust me most of them wish they were euthanized there's absolutely no reason why you should be feeling guilty Theory of conduct Animal euthanasia Euthanasia Lethal injection Garfield Kodocha Animal shelter Cat Pet skunk Pitaten Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Social rule EastEnders Characters in the Smurfs Days of our Lives Abortion debate Shaggy dog story Organ transplant Diabetes mellitus Ferret Evil Time Out of Mind Zoophilia Pneumonia 1957 World Series Final Fantasy: Unlimited Original sin Goodness and value theory Dialysis Anorexia nervosa Prostate cancer Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Weight training American Psycho Obedience training The Fairly OddParents Summa Theologiae Jon Sec